Colour dark yellow generally. Antennae brown darker apically, head reddish dorsally, with 3 canary ocellated markings, face becoming crimson from fastigium frons to clypeus, labrum reddish brown and mandibles yellowish brown, compound eyes darkish brown (
Fig. 3a, e
, 
Fig. 5a
); pronotum darker with reddish brown margin also inconspicuous stripes and middle marking (
Fig. 5a
); folded wings yellowish brown dorsally with looming darkish patches, almost transparent laterally (
Fig. 5
); legs only with margins of femora and tibia getting brown, tip of spines, claws and spurs of hind tibia black, tarsi darkish yellow, movable spines and spurs of walking legs little darker (
Fig. 5
); tegmina almost transparent, pale brown, unfolded wings also transparent but dark brown in cell, transverse veins behind R base and Rs blackish brown with translucent black markings bordered on both sides (
Fig. 2a, d
); ovipositor base yellow, medium part brown, apical third with margins and top black (
Fig. 5
).
